        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "Zend_Db_Select::where() should be able to accept arrays as input...\n\nThis can simplify input like in the following example:\nold:\n{code}\n$db->where('column1 = ?', 2)\n       ->where('column2 = ?', 5)\n       ->where('column3 = ?', 10);\n{code}\n\nsimplified:\n{code}\n$array = array(\n    'column1' => 2,\n    'column2' => 5,\n    'column3' => 10);\n$db->where($array);\n{code}\n\nThis is of course only supported if named arrays are given.\nThe values from numeric arrays would be used for replacing existing placeholders"
        },
